    <h3> History Of Singapore</h3>
  </head>
  <body>
    <a href="index.html">Back to Home</a>
    <p> Singapore was found in the early 19th century. The last ruler of the Kingdom of Singapura, Parameswara, was expelled by the Majapahit or the Siamese before he founded Malacca. This Island Came under the Malacca Sultanate. In 1819, British statesman Stamford Raffles negotiated a treaty whereby Johor would allow the British to locate a trading port on the island, ultimately leading to the establishment of the Crown colony of Singapore in 1867. During the World War 2 Singapore was invaded by the Japanese Empire.</p>
    <p> Singapore reverted to British control, with increasing levels of self-government being granted, resulting in Singapore's merger with the Federation of Malaya to form Malaysia in 1963.Singapore became an independent republic on 9 August 1965.the country had established a highly developed free market economy and strong international trading links. It now has the highest per capita gross domestic product in Asia, which is 7th in the world, and it is ranked 9th on the UN Human Development Index.</p>
